Description: Fix CVE-2026-5588 - PKIX draft CompositeVerifier accepts empty signature sequence
 The generic composite signature verifier in JcaContentVerifierProviderBuilder
 could return a positive verification result without actually checking any
 signature (e.g., when given an empty signature sequence). The fix introduces
 an `atLeastOneChecked` flag and ANDs it into the return value so that
 verify() returns false when no signature was actually verified.
 Backported from upstream commit 656bae0 (released in BouncyCastle 1.84).
 The target uses DERBitString.getBytes() (1.70 API) which is preserved
 unchanged; only the security guard is added. A regression test
 (testForgedComposite) is added; testComposite from upstream is omitted
 because it depends on ML-DSA APIs not present in 1.70.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/bcgit/bc-java/commit/656bae0dbd9b1521f840521ff786e78749fe3057
Author: David Hook <dgh@cryptoworkshop.com>
Last-Update: 2026-06-24

diff --git a/pkix/src/main/java/org/bouncycastle/operator/jcajce/JcaContentVerifierProviderBuilder.java b/pkix/src/main/java/org/bouncycastle/operator/jcajce/JcaContentVerifierProviderBuilder.java
index 8f2102b..6ae7756 100644
--- a/pkix/src/main/java/org/bouncycastle/operator/jcajce/JcaContentVerifierProviderBuilder.java
+++ b/pkix/src/main/java/org/bouncycastle/operator/jcajce/JcaContentVerifierProviderBuilder.java
@@ -429,17 +429,20 @@ public boolean verify(byte[] expected)
             {
                 ASN1Sequence sigSeq = ASN1Sequence.getInstance(expected);
                 boolean failed = false;
+                boolean atLeastOneChecked = false;
+
                 for (int i = 0; i != sigSeq.size(); i++)
                 {
                     if (sigs[i] != null)
                     {
+                        atLeastOneChecked = true;
                         if (!sigs[i].verify(DERBitString.getInstance(sigSeq.getObjectAt(i)).getBytes()))
                         {
                             failed = true;
                         }
                     }
                 }
-                return !failed;
+                return !failed & atLeastOneChecked;
             }
             catch (SignatureException e)
             {
